                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.5151/277: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-28T11:00:00-04:30"
                            >August 28, 1937—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>755. My 753, August 27, 5 p.m. The Director of the Exchange Bureau informed me
                    this morning that virtually all peseta deposits awaiting dollar exchange are in
                    private banks and that the banks and not the Government are responsible
                    therefor. He was, of course, not aware of my conversation with Negrín
                    yesterday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
